This is a hostage rescue mission in a dark urban suburb. The people have evacuated as the terrorist's attack. But some could not be rescued. You must save the final 4 civilians before the terrorists arrive.

This is not a final release. There are still some small bugs and mishaps to fix up, and the lights are not final. Also, there is a lot of detail I plan to add in in the final release. This is a completely finished layout of the map, which means there is only aesthetics to add in.

It is a hostage rescue map, with four hostages needing rescue. The rescue zone is a snack store located by the Counter-Terrorist spawn zone. Just let the train tracks act as your North Star as you find your way back.

There is a Counter-Terrorist block of buildings nested under train tracks, a small shantyville shielded underneath wooded roofing, and a red building infested with Terrorists. There are 3 alleyways to get from one side to the other, with a few entryways to each.

The skybox is absolute garbage right now, and its only placeholder. As well as the lighting.

give it a try and please rate and let me know what you think.

This is an updated version of the original cs_spetsnaz featured in the Official FilePlanet Source Mappack. Spawns have been increased to 32 and minor layout changes have been made to balance gameplay due to people camping around hostages by adding a window on the third floor, optimized it to run more efficiently, and fixed all the minor bugs. 

Scenario: 

Set in Grozny, Russia. Chechen warlord Shamil Basayev has taken hostages and is holding them within a compound disguised as an ordinary warehouse. After days of failed negotiations, the Russian spetsnaz special operations team has been signaled to engage the compound. Engage the enemy by dropping thru the ceiling windows, side windows, vents, roof top sniper battles, and best of all, night vision... 

NOTE: There is a power switch on west exterior side of the building which can shut off the interior lighting. Use the lever on the power box and engage the enemy with nightvision.

This map uses the formula found in many hostage situations: Counter-Terrorists must assault, clear and rescue hostages in a large warehouse.

Don't dismiss this map as just an assault clone, it is much more than that. The Counter-Terrorists start off on the street while the Terrorists start off in their facility. Just a short rush brings the CTs to a electric gate... which is suicide if the terrorists have any common sense. There are entrences in the back as well.

Once in the building the Counter-Terrorists have to clear three stories to reach the hostages. Due to the close quarters of this map, it seems to me that it would be very hard for a terrorist to sneak around and lay a trap in the hostage rescue point, but it can be done.

The map itself is well made, the time setting and atmostphere is great. The texture selection for the interior and exterior of the warehouse is excellent. The Exterior has that degraded, old look to it while the inside is clean and new, just what you would expect from a criminal organization's safehouse.

Here is an 8 year attempt at bringing the majority of my previously unfinished and finished CSS maps together to create something of an epic map.

This is in no way the finished product. However due to current time commitments and the age of the game, I am not going to be working on the map any longer. I will reconsider if the beta is popular enough.

It is laggy, glitchy, buggy, the AI sucks (especially the hostages) and terribly made. However it is massive, there are tons of easter eggs and fun things to do. It may make a better hide and go seek map, or perhaps even a good death match map. You decide.

In any case, feel free to let me know if any improvements you would like to see in this or any future map by myself. Please have some fun with all the hours I've put into this map.

I'm not going to update this map anymore so if there's something you think needs changing, feel free to do so yourself by downloading the .vfm here. There's 32 spawn points (Maybe 40. cs_smuggler by JP

Map made by JP from rhode island.
Setting: Night
Hosties are in the warehouse/building.
Map features: Underground tunnels, Trash dumpsters, backalley ways, Roof tops, broken cars, accessable doors, interiors on rooms, a park, and more.

CT's should rush the building fast for a better chance of winning, or rush the alley ways and flank the building from its tail.
T's should rush building as well and rush upstairs to cover the hosties and make sure the CT's dont walk away with them.

Night vision is recommended in this map to have a better view of enemy's. when inside I strongly recommend turning night vision off.
Map took about 2 weeks of work, I hope you all enjoy..

Fixes: 
-hosties now move and yes, there is a nav file for bots.
-Lighting is working smoothly
-More access ways to building for a more realistic look

Thanks

-JP

Hi All,

I am relasing this map retrospectively. I actually made this map back in 2007 but at the time I never relased it ( I didnt know banana at the time and I thought that the map wasnt really good enough - but having seen what other people are prepared to release, I dont think that'll be a problem!). 

This was the first full sized map I ever completed and as such I lacked alot of the experience I have today. If I were to remake this now I would definitely do alot off stuff differently.

The map is all dev texture and I should probably explain this. At the time I made this there were alot, I mean a hell of alot of dev textured maps out there on servers... they were very, very popular. As a player the first time I saw a dev map I was really impressed, i thought wow these guys must really know what they are doing (! yeah, I know, lol). As a mapper I quickly discovered that making dev maps was kind of a cop-out... texturing a map well, even a little gg or fy map is hard. So by making this I was atempting to make a dev textured map that was a bit more sophisticated... more than just walls and blocks, a dev map that was still a real-world environment. Today you generally see alot less dev maps than before, but whatever.

Like is said, this map was my first ever effort, so its not perfect, but basically it works and I thought maybe people could have some fun with it.

I hope that you enjoy it.

K@rt

This is a playable port of cs_siege from 1.6.  I decompiled the original map then went through and replaced the old textures with CS:S textures.  I also redid all of the lighting entities as they did not decompile properly. 

Additionally:
-Doors Removed
-T base reduced in size
-Two hostage rescue zones (bridge and tunnel end)
-Moved hostages into garage for balance
-Map seems to lag in some spots (tweet me @vybeypantelonez if you know how to fix that), but is fully playable.
-Some spots simplified, still func_detail-ing the map though
-Still a WIP but looks decent

Will be releasing the .vmf file tomorrow but I'm too tired to do it now.

Remake of cs_siege with some extra stuff in it. I'm going to be adding some extra areas to this. The layout is pretty much the same except that you've got an access tunnel that leads to a power station that you can blow up and cut power to the entire level. This will disable all the lights inside the buildings. You can also toggle the lights for the garage, the warehouse, and the sewers in this version. The switches are located at the warehouse enterance to the sewer, and also at the garage enterance to the sewer. The map geometry is constructed for the most part. I am currently optimizing the map, and making the lighting look good. I'm also adding things to spice up the rooms.
